==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perplexity
<hw>Per*plex"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Perplexities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>perplexitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>perplexit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being perplexed or puzzled; complication; intricacy; entanglement; distraction of mind through doubt or difficulty; embarrassment; bewilderment; doubt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By their own <qex>perplexities</qex> involved,⟦br⟧
They ravel more.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perplexiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
